						<button class="faq-question">
							Do I need a crypto wallet to participate?
							<span class="faq-icon">üëõ</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>Yes, you'll need a compatible crypto wallet to mint and hold your Everdantia trees. We'll provide detailed guides and support to help newcomers set up their wallets safely.</p>
							<p>Don't worry if you're new to crypto‚Äîour community is here to help guide you through the process!</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Conservation Callout -->
			<div class="faq-callout">
				<h4>üåç Our Conservation Commitment</h4>
				<p>We donate a significant portion of all proceeds to verified reforestation and conservation organizations. Every tree you mint directly contributes to protecting and restoring real forests worldwide.</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Conservation -->
			<section id="conservation" class="faq-section">
				<h2 class="section-title">üåç Conservation Impact</h2>
				<div class="faq-grid">
					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question">
							How do NFT sales support real conservation?
							<span class="faq-icon">üå±</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>We commit a substantial percentage of net proceeds from every mint to verified conservation organizations. For our Genesis Collection, we're dedicating 50% of net proceeds to our first conservation partner.</p>
							<p>All donations are tracked transparently in our public Forest Ledger, where you can see proof of donations, partner organizations, and even GPS coordinates of protected or restored areas.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="faq-item">
						<button class="faq-question">
							Which conservation organizations do you support?
							<span class="faq-icon">ü§ù</span>
						</button>
						<div class="faq-answer">
							<p>We're currently in discussions with several local reforestation initiatives and international conservation NGOs. We carefully evaluate potential partners based on their transparency, track record, and measurable impact.</p>
							<p>Partner announcements will be made on our blog and community channels as partnerships are finalized.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

